         Crédit Agricole CIB, the Corporate & Investment Banking arm of Crédit Agricole S.A, (CACIB), offers its clients worldwide a broad range of products and services in capital markets, investment banking, and commercial banking. The bank has a comprehensive and growing business franchise in many emerging markets. 


         The proposed transaction is expected to have a tenor of up to 5 years and consists of up to US$85 million of un-funded IFC risk participation in an approximate US$2 billion global portfolio of predominantly emerging markets trade finance-related credit assets on CACIBs balance sheet. This risk participation will support further growth in CACIBs trade finance and social projects in emerging markets.

